parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel tank leak or failure can cause fuel to spill onto the ground, creating a fire hazard and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.

unable to fill the tank with fuel

fuel fill overflow valve stops working correctly
unable to fill the tank with fuel.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Head Gasket Failure and Engine Damage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head gasket can cause coolant leaks, engine damage, and potentially lead to engine failure, which can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the airbag module can cause the airbag light to illuminate, indicating a potential safety risk, and may lead to airbag deployment failure in the event of an accident.
The failure of the transmission can cause unintended acceleration, loss of control, and potentially lead to accidents.
The failure of the transmission and cruise control can cause loss of speed, loss of control, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Cruise control fails to maintain speed

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the 4WD system can cause loss of control, particularly when turning at low speeds, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Difficulty turning left or right when 4WD is engaged
hard to turn at low speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag system can lead to failure to deploy or incorrect deployment in the event of a crash, potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag light remains on or flashes
the airbag light turns off only when the vehicle is turned off
the passenger airbag is disabled despite an adult occupant
the airbag deploys incorrectly or fails to deploy in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the roof rack can cause the rack to detach from the vehicle, leading to accidents, damage to the vehicle, and potential harm to passengers or other road users.
symptoms: The roof rack detaches from the vehicle
causing damage to the vehicle and its contents
and potentially leading to accidents or near-misses.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The entry of fumes and odors into the cabin can cause dizziness, disorientation, and distraction while driving, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Strong fumes and odors enter the cabin

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rodent damage to wiring can cause electrical system failures, leading to accidents, fires, or other safety hazards.
The failure of the bed extender can cause the extender to detach from the vehicle, leading to accidents, damage to the vehicle, and potential harm to passengers or other road users.
symptoms: The bed extender detaches from the vehicle
causing damage to the vehicle and its contents
and potentially leading to accidents or near-misses.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause the vehicle to stall without warning, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents. Additionally, the failure can cause dash lights to remain on even with the key out of the ignition, and prevent doors from unlocking, which can lead to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: dash lights remain on even with the key out of the ignition
the engine primes without a key in the ignition
the radio plays without a key in the ignition
the digital mileage display shows up without a key in the ignition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speedometer can cause the driver to be unaware of their speed, which can lead to accidents or traffic violations.
symptoms: The speedometer needle is stuck on zero
the odometer and other gauges work normally.
